  <header>
    <h1 class="er-leading-tight er-text-8xl er-font-base mb:er-text-5xl mb:er-leading-tight er-text-center">Urtopia Privacy Policy</h1>
  </header>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how New Urtopia Holdings HK Limited (“Urtopia”, “we”, “us”, or “our”) collects, uses,
    shares and processes your personal data as well as the rights and choices you have associated with that data.
    Urtopia is committed to protecting your privacy and personal data. We encourage you to read this Privacy Policy to
    understand what we do with the personal data we collect from you and how we keep you safe. This Privacy Policy
    applies to the use of Urtopia website, App and products (collectively, the “Services”), effective from March 14,
    2022. From time to time, you may be able to follow a link to the websites or services of other companies or
    individuals from our website or our App. These companies or individuals may collect your personal data in accordance
    with their own privacy policies. Urtopia’s Privacy Policy does not extend to these external websites, services and
    third parties.
  </p>
  <h2>This Privacy Policy Discusses:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>How We Collect and Use Personal Data</li>
    <li>How We Share Personal Data We Collect</li>
    <li>Our Data Security and Storage Practices</li>
    <li>How We Store and Transfer Your Personal Data</li>
    <li>Your Choices Regarding the Use of Your Personal Data</li>
    <li>Minors’ Personal Data</li>
    <li>Privacy Policy Updates</li>
    <li>How You Can Contact Us</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We have tried to keep this policy as simple and easy-to-read as possible. If you have any questions, please contact
    us at <a href="/pages/contactus" target="_self">support@newurtopia.com.</a>
  </p>
  <h2>1. How We Collect and Use Personal Data</h2>
  <p>
    In this privacy policy, personal data means any data relating to an identified or identifiable natural person as
    defined in the law of the country or region of your residence.
  </p>
  <h3>1.1 We Collect Personal Data When You Use Our Website</h3>
  <p>
    When you use our website, we may collect a variety of personal data from or about you to provide services to you.
    For example,
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      When you purchase Urtopia’s products from our website, we will collect and use your name, phone number, address,
      e-mail address to fulfill your request for products, or to send you notifications, confirmations, updates, product
      announcements, and security alerts. We may also use such personal data to create an account for you. If you are a
      resident of European Economic Area (“EEA”), we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the General
      Data Protection Regulation (“GDPR”), i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract.
    </li>
    <li>
      When you register on the mailing list or for our newsletter, your email address will be added to our contact list.
      If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(a) of the GDPR, i.e., data
      subjects’ consent.
    </li>
    <li>
      When you send us an email to participate in our surveys, request help from customer support, or otherwise submit
      information to us through our website, in order to respond to your communications and requests, provide customer
      service, request feedback, and otherwise contact you about your use of our Service, we may collect your e-mail and
      other personal data that you directly provide to us, such as your name, telephone number and address. If you are a
      resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(a) of GDPR, i.e., data subjects’ consent.
    </li>
    <li>
      When you request an exchange or refund, we may collect additional personal data about payment details and reasons
      for requesting an exchange or refund. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article
      6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract.
    </li>
    <li>
      When you use our website, we may collect your browsing behaviors to improve the performance or design of our
      website. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(d) of the GDPR, i.e.,
      necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller.
    </li>
    <li>
      When you use any of the public comment or interactive features of our website, we may collect any information you
      provide to us. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(a) of GDPR, i.e.,
      data subjects’ consent.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h3>1.2 We Collect Personal Data When You Use Our App and Products</h3>
  <p>
    Urtopia is proud of its futuristic design and smart functions. When you use our App and our products, or when you
    connect your bike with your Urtopia Account, we may collect your personal data to provide services to you. Depending
    on which services or features you request or use, not all of these types of personal data may be applicable to you.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      When you sign up for a Urtopia Account (“Account”), you may provide us with a combination of personal data, such
      as your e-mail, name or nickname, and password. You may also choose to provide us with additional personal data,
      such as your phone number, address, birthday, and gender. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on
      the basis of Article 6.1(a) of GDPR, i.e., data subjects’ consent.
    </li>
    <li>
      You may provide location data of the e-bike to us, which is necessary to enable navigation, anti-theft and
      find-my-bike functions. For navigation purpose and find-my-bike functions, if you are a resident of EEA, we
      process such location data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a
      contract. For anti-theft purpose, if you are a resident of EEA, we process such location data on the basis of
      Article 6.1(d) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the
      controller.
    </li>
    <li>
      We may use your fingerprint information to enable you to unlock your bike, and such information is only stored on
      your bike and will not be transferred to us. You can also use your cellphone to unlock your bike, and we may use
      your Bluetooth information to provide such feature. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the
      basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract.
    </li>
    <li>
      You can interact with the e-bike by pressing a certain button and speaking to it. We may capture audio voice
      recordings and voice commands during those interactions. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the
      basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract. We cannot prevent you from
      providing additional personal data when you interact with the e-bike.
    </li>
    <li>
      We may collect your audio voice recordings and voice commands, when you use voice control feature in your e-bike.
      If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for
      the performance of a contract.
    </li>
    <li>
      Our e-bike carries a bunch of IoT sensors including torque sensor, gyroscope, mm-wave radar and GPS. You may sync
      data collected from such sensors and other bike stats data, such as, speed, distance, battery level, boot screen,
      ringing sound, motor power, slope, etc. to your Account on our App. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such
      data on the basis of Article 6.1(b) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the performance of a contract. We may use
      such data to improve your riding experience and to provide more fascinating features on our App. If you are a
      resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(d) of the GDPR, i.e., necessary for the purposes
      of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller.
    </li>
    <li>
      We may collect device numbers of your e-bike, such as hardware serial number, MAC address, and unique device
      identifier to check status of your e-bike when you request for after-sales service and provide relevant service to
      you. If you are a resident of EEA, we process such data on the basis of Article 6.1(d) of the GDPR, i.e.,
      necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h3>1.3 How We Use Cookies and Similar Technologies</h3>
  <p>
    Like most web-based services, we automatically receive and record information on our server logs from your browser
    when you use our website. We may use a variety of methods, including beacons and cookies, to collect your personal
    data. The personal data that we collect with these automated methods may include, for example, your IP address,
    cookie data, a unique device or user ID, browser type, system type, the content and pages that you access on our
    website, and the “referring URL” (that is, the page from which you navigated to our website). Please see our cookie
    policy for more details.
  </p>
  <h3>1.4 We Collect Personal Data from Third Parties</h3>
  <p>
    To the extent permitted by applicable law, we may combine personal data with other personal data we collect from
    your activity in our Services, personal data we receive from other companies or publicly available personal data.
  </p>
  <h3>1.5 We Aggregate and Anonymize Personal Data</h3>
  <p>
    We may use personal data we collect in aggregated forms. That is, we may combine personal data about our users with
    that of others in an anonymous manner to create aggregate data. Aggregate data does not contain or constitute
    personal data. In such cases, there will be no identifying data disclosed about you. When we entrust non-Urtopia
    companies to anonymize or aggregate data on our behalf, we will oversee their personal data processing through
    contractual arrangements to ensure adequate protection of your personal data. We will not identify your identity,
    except in accordance with this Privacy Policy. We do not sell personalized demographic data or user data.
  </p>
  <h3>1.6 Public Comment and User Generated Content</h3>
  <p>
    We provide public comment features and other interactive features to share user generated content on our website and
    App. Please note that any information you post or disclose using this feature will become public information, and
    will be available to other users of our Services and to the general public. We urge you to be very careful when
    deciding to disclose your personal data, or any other information. If you provide feedback to us, we may use and
    disclose such feedback on our website, provided we do not associate such feedback with your personal data. If you
    have provided your consent to do so, we may post your first and last name along with your feedback on our website.
    We will collect any information contained in such feedback and will treat the personal data in it in accordance with
    this Policy.
  </p>
  <h2>2. How We Share Personal Data We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    We are committed to protecting data that identifies you personally, where you have chosen to keep it private. We
    will only share your personal data in the following circumstances:<br>
    With Urtopia service providers. Urtopia hires several service providers to help operate our Services (including
    vendors and payment processors), and may give access to certain personal data necessary for service providers to
    undertake their work, in which case we will require those service providers to honor the privacy and your personal
    data. Urtopia currently uses the following third-party service providers to provide their services:<br>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Vendors who provide platform service. Our website is hosted on Shopify Inc. Shopify provides us with the online
      e-commerce platform that allows us to sell our products to you. Your personal data may be stored through Shopify’s
      data storage and databases. For more insight, you may also want to read Shopify’s Terms of Service or Privacy
      Policy.
    </li>
    <li>
      Vendors who provide delivery service. We may share your contact information, such as address and phone number with
      these vendors to fulfill delivering products.
    </li>
    <li>
      Vendors who provide voice recognition technology. We may share your audio voice recordings with these vendors to
      generate voice commands and enable you to use voice control features.
    </li>
    <li>
      Vendors who provide email service. We may share your e-mail address with these vendors, such as MailChimp, to send
      you marketing messages, notifications, confirmations, updates, product announcements, and security alerts.
    </li>
    <li>
      Vendors who provide analytics services. Our website uses analytics services, such as Fabric, a software
      development and integration kit that allows Urtopia to analyze its customers’ general usage patterns, including
      the rates of Urtopia users on daily and weekly bases.
    </li>
    <li>
      Vendors who provide payment service. Our website uses Klarna for alternative payment options. You can read more
      about how Klarna uses your personal information here:
      <a href="https://www.klarna.com/international/privacy-policy/" target="_blank"
        >https://www.klarna.com/international/privacy-policy/</a
      >
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    With Urtopia partners. We may share some of your personal data with our partners (including a parent company,
    subsidiaries, other companies that we control or that are under common control with us, and joint venture partners),
    in which case we will require those partners to honor your personal data.<br>
    <br>
    In the event of merger or sale. If Urtopia is involved in a merger, acquisition, bankruptcy, or any form of sale of
    some or all of its business, personal data may be transferred with the business.<br>
    <br>
    When legally obligated or to protect from harm. Urtopia may share personal data when we have a good faith that
    access, use, preservation or disclosure of the personal data is reasonably necessary to (a) satisfy any requirement
    of law, regulation, legal process or enforceable governmental request; (b) enforce or investigate a potential
    violation of the Terms of Use; (c) detect, prevent or otherwise respond to fraud, security or technical concerns; or
    (d) protect the rights, property or safety of Urtopia, its users or the public against harm.<br>
  </p>
  <h2>3. Our Data Security and Storage Practices</h2>
  <p>
    We work hard to protect Urtopia and our users from unauthorized access to or unauthorized alteration, disclosure or
    destruction of personal data we hold. Urtopia follows industry standards and best practices to help protect your
    personal data from unauthorized access, use and disclosure. For example, we store the personal data we collect on
    computer systems with limited access and located in controlled facilities. When we transmit highly-confidential
    personal data over the Internet, we protect it through the use of encryption, such as the Secure Socket Layer (SSL)
    protocol. Please be aware that, despite our efforts, no security measures are impenetrable. Unfortunately, we cannot
    guarantee that any method of data transmission will protect against any interception or other type of misuse.
  </p>
  <h2>4. How We Store and Transfer Your Personal Data</h2>
  <p>
    Urtopia stores and processes personal data in databases hosted in the country or region in compliance with
    applicable laws. We will only retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which
    it was collected and to the extent permitted or required by law.<br>
    <br>
    In some circumstances, we will, subject to law, transfer your personal data to other countries or regions where you
    reside or allow entities outside of countries or regions where you reside to access your personal data. Any such
    transfer of your personal data will be carried out in compliance with applicable laws.<br>
  </p>
  <h2>5. Your Choices Regarding the Use of Your Personal Data</h2>
  <p>
    You may request access to and correction of your personal data we retain. If you request that we delete personal
    data, such personal data will be permanently deleted, and we will no longer retain that personal data in any form.
    If you wish to stop further collection or use of your personal data, or to delete your email address, you may choose
    to permanently delete your Account by emailing us at support@newurtopia.com. Please note that, by permanently
    deleting your Account, you will disable most of the advanced functionality of the Urtopia e-bike. To reinstate
    functionality at a later date, you may set up a new Account. You may also opt out of receiving emails from us
    anytime by following the unsubscribe instructions in those emails.<br>
    <br>
    In addition, depending on applicable law, you have the right to submit a complaint or object to our collection and
    use of your information at any time, or to require us to review, transmit, change, or delete your personal data that
    we have collected and retained. We will fulfill your request to exercise any of these rights within the applicable
    time period subscribed by such laws. You can exercise these rights, express concerns, or obtain additional
    information about the use of your personal data by contacting us.<br>
  </p>
  <h3>5.1 Your rights under GDPR or Data Protection Act 2018</h3>
  <p>If you are a resident in the EEA or the United Kingdom, you have the following rights:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Right to Access. You may request access to the personal data we process about you;</li>
    <li>
      Right to Correct and Delete. You may request us to correct, update, shield or delete your personal data in our
      records;
    </li>
    <li>
      Right to Request a Copy. You may request a copy of the personal data we have processed about you. We can - on your
      request - send this copy to another party, so you don’t have to send the personal data yourself;
    </li>
    <li>
      Object to processing. You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data and request us to cease
      processing of it if, for example, this data is being processed for the purpose of direct marketing or where we are
      relying on a legitimate interest (or those of a third party). In some cases, we may demonstrate that we have
      compelling legitimate grounds to process your data which override your rights and freedoms.
    </li>
    <li>
      Restrict the processing. This enables you to ask us to suspend the processing of your personal data in the
      following scenarios: (a) if you want us to establish the accuracy of the personal data; (b) where our use of the
      data is unlawful but you do not want us to erase it; (c) where you require us to hold the data even if we no
      longer need it as you require it to establish, exercise or defend legal claims; or (d) you have objected to our
      use of your data but we need to verify whether we have overriding legitimate grounds to use it.
    </li>
    <li>
      Right to Complain. You may file a complaint against processing your personal data. And you may file a complaint if
      you are under the impression that we process your data unlawfully;
    </li>
    <li>
      Withdraw Your Consent. You may always withdraw your consent to process your personal data. In that case, we will
      no longer process your personal data for the purpose for which consent is necessary.
    </li>
    <li>Requesting channels. Please email us at support@newurtopia.com to submit your data request.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>5.2 California Privacy Rights</h3>
  <p>
    Urtopia adopted this section to comply with the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 (“CCPA”) and the California
    Privacy Rights Act (“CPRA”), and applies solely to residents of the State of California (“California Consumers”).
    Without limiting the foregoing, this section provides California Consumers with the disclosures and notices required
    under the CCPA. Certain exceptions and limitations may apply to a California Consumer’s rights and Urtopia’s
    obligations under the CCPA.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      No Sale of Personal Data. If Urtopia ever chooses to sell personal data, you would have the right to opt out of
      the sale of your personal data.
    </li>
    <li>
      Right to Disclosure. California Consumers have the right to request that we disclose certain data about our
      collection and use of your personal data over the past 12 months.
    </li>
    <li>
      Right to Access. You have the right to request that we provide you with access to specific pieces of personal data
      we have collected about you over the past 12 months (also called a “data portability request”).
    </li>
    <li>
      Right to Deletion. You have the right to request that we delete any of your personal data that we collected from
      you and retained, with certain exceptions.
    </li>
    <li>
      Right to Correct. You have the right to request us to correct inaccurate personal data if and when you learn that
      we maintain inaccurate personal data about you.
    </li>
    <li>
      Right Against Discrimination. You have the right not to be discriminated against for exercising any of the rights
      described in this section. We will not discriminate against you for exercising your right.
    </li>
    <li>
      Right to Limit the Use of Sensitive Personal Information. Some of personal data we collect and use in accordance
      with purposes described in this Privacy Policy might fall into the scope of sensitive personal data as defined by
      CPRA. The use of such sensitive personal data will be limited to that use that is necessary for us to provide
      Services to you or perform our duties as required by CCPA and CPRA. If we may use your sensitive personal data for
      any other purpose, we will inform you and you have the right to limit the use of your sensitive personal data.
      Upon your request, we will not use your sensitive personal data for the proposed additional purpose.
    </li>
    <li>
      Submit a Consumer Privacy Request. To exercise any of the above rights, please submit a verifiable consumer
      privacy request to Urtopia by email at support@newurtopia.com.
    </li>
    <li>
      Verification. We cannot respond to your request or provide you with personal data unless we can verify your
      identity and your authority to make the request and confirm that the personal data relates to you.
    </li>
    <li>
      Authorized Agent. You may make a verifiable consumer request on behalf of your minor child. Otherwise, only you,
      or a person you have designated in writing as your authorized agent or who is registered with the California
      Secretary of State to act on your behalf, or to whom you have provided power of attorney pursuant to California
      Probate Code sections 4000 to 4465 (“Authorized Agent”) may make a verifiable consumer request related to your
      personal data.
    </li>
    <li>
      Urtopia’s Response. We endeavor to respond to a verifiable consumer request within 45 days of receipt. If we
      require more time, we will notify you in writing of the reason and extension period. We will deliver our written
      response by mail or electronically, at your option. Any disclosures we provide will only cover the 12-month period
      preceding receipt of the verifiable consumer request. If we cannot comply with part or all of your request, we
      will explain the reasons in our response. We do not charge a fee to process or respond to your verifiable consumer
      privacy request unless it is excessive, repetitive, or manifestly unfounded. If we determine that the request
      warrants a fee, we will tell you why we made that decision and provide you with a cost estimate before completing
      your request.
    </li>
    <li>
      Other California Privacy Rights. California Civil Code sections 1798.83-1798.84 (the Shine the Light Act) entitles
      California residents to request disclosure regarding personal data sharing with affiliates and/or third parties
      for marketing purposes. If you are a California resident and you would like to request a copy of this notice,
      please contact us at support@newurtopia.com with the subject line “Request for California Privacy Data.”
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h3>5.3 Nevada Privacy Rights</h3>
  <p>
    If you are a Nevada resident and have provided us with any personal identifying data, you may opt-out of sharing
    your data with third parties if you submit an opt-out request to the following email address:
    support@newurtopia.com. Please note we do not sell any of your personal data for profit, we do share some data with
    contracted third parties in order to provide better services and advertising to you. Please allow 60 days for
    completion of such request.
  </p>
  <h2>6. Minors’ Personal Data</h2>
  <p>
    Our Services are designed for adults, not children. As such, our Services are not intended for children under 16
    years of age. No one under age 16 may provide any personal data to us or in our Services. If you are under 16, do
